<subSubSection id="79BAA1F890F9FF3E5F5ED070566AB98C" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A1231138E620C00CB3ED30A295575923" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6ACDD702E044A13D9D17703717435B2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="39F417CCABCCC6A616B18FD6A0764103" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia rhoigena" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rhoigena">
<emphasis id="F28DD7F41367A64A31A0090469D3102D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia rhoigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other gnomoniaceous species by the formation of synnemata.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D05C5DE5361FB725EBE9A35E8A28DFDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3ECF8C41F9ACECEFE245C7DA9B7B75BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B4AE61099EBE069405DF4B9AB2FAA01" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Named after the host genus, 
<taxonomicName id="FE5C8B4FF1F21ACA3D69D2672E403C48" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Rhus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhus" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1CC0D869B36F99A169E1C8CF753E1870" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Rhus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4209BF0A850E5368D3B039F9E4D44B54" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="4717FE70F47CA49B1A375EFF0457BC87" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB517AE7377C0A32BE71A01E03AA8DFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Sexual morph: not observed. Asexual morph: Conidiomata synnematal. Synnemata (650
<normalizedToken id="409976BC841362BDC638DB789C30E651" originalValue="–)750–">-)750-</normalizedToken>
1100 
<normalizedToken id="6017F287DC770363E7A02F719D957117" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
high, 150-300 
<normalizedToken id="8E5057CAEDC0ED4224A0972653909637" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam, determinate, growing from host tissue, with brown base and orange tip, straight to curved, parallel, with flat to slightly concave and dark zone of conidiogenous cells and host tissue at their bases. Conidiophores reduced to conidiogenous cells. Conidiogenous cells (12.5
<normalizedToken id="91370039F665C08E1D3A1CABC90CC6D4" originalValue="–)16–22(–">-)16-22(-</normalizedToken>
25) 
<normalizedToken id="8714189DC28A34EA1C26AAE3638EB596" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 
<normalizedToken id="80A2B902F633040B22706777726234B7" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, phialidic, aggregated, hyaline, straight to curved, cylindrical, arranged adjacent to one another at the end of the synnema, producing a single conidium. Conidia cylindrical to oblong, smooth, multiguttulate, hyaline, (5
<normalizedToken id="B6A8F26796EB411BB033E05E964D6BE5" originalValue="–)5.5–7(–">-)5.5-7(-</normalizedToken>
8) 
<normalizedToken id="6865DEFD6FD294C57B8D820046F5FB24" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2 
<normalizedToken id="6A6D830F22BCC6FF3669D936076981F3" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84FFABF2CD601109CE7E0A9ADFC013BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="B7155D401531C499BA13E0B607E1A076" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Culture characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8AC503BB09AF9455B8B3EC813E758201" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">On PDA at 25 °C in darkness, initially white, becoming olive-green to black after 3 wk, zonate with 3-4 well defined zones. Conidiomata distributed concentrically over agar surface.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C2218456407CD83B8A787B74D2144FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="specimen examined">
<paragraph id="0408B58921A8F7D9DBA6AC61B415E108" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Specimen examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8F124BCDAC21B85795D740BC1D76B14" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
CHINA, Jiangxi Province, Ganzhou City, Xunwu County, 
<geoCoordinate id="5BD46931793CAE9C7EB83F6F15156795" degrees="24" direction="north" minutes="52" orientation="latitude" precision="1" seconds="31.34" value="24.875372">24°52'31.34&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="9DA16E3ED055887719DB155DDB1EEE81" degrees="115" direction="east" minutes="35" orientation="longitude" precision="1" seconds="39.53" value="115.594315">115°35'39.53&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, on branches of 
<taxonomicName id="012D60FB041BC3AAE16C3F9F3D017603" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Rhus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhus chinensis" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="521FE967D9DE766027F0153D668AA625" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Rhus chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 14 May 2018, Q. Yang, Y. Liu &amp; Y.M. Liang (holotype BJFC-S1766, ex-type living cultures CFCC 53118, CFCC 53119 and CFCC 53120).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1E53C132CDAB2B3E785CFE35CDEE3996" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="notes">
<paragraph id="241E14CB9BB49F97D2AD467124817D76" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9269F54F115A5B13E5F7038C51C262C" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="A1C7DAF6C8CD83B2810F333F31715A33" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia rhoigena" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rhoigena">
<emphasis id="0349BB1F4B8798A2A710F19611B5DE76" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia rhoigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the type species of 
<taxonomicName id="3ACEDEEB60B775C63C2A6ABB024F6612" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="634580959F63B030CBA4E0680CB7BAF3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the family 
<taxonomicName id="BAD2AECEF11CCE8F7B906B6B50B8BD0E" family="Gnomoniaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="family">Gnomoniaceae</taxonomicName>
. It can be easily distinguished from the other gnomoniaceous genera by its unique conidiomata (Walker et al. 2004, 
<bibRefCitation id="DF524FB9A3485449BBB6A4640CD50FE9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-018-0410-z" author="Senanayake, IC" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="241 - 443" refId="B23" refString="Senanayake, IC, Jeewon, R, Chomnunti, P, Wanasinghe, DN, Norphanphoun, C, Karunarathna, A, Pem, D, Perera, RH, Camporesi, E, McKenzie, EHC, Hyde, KD, Karunarathna, SC, 2018. Taxonomic circumscription of Diaporthales based on multigene phylogeny and morphology. Fungal Diversity 93: 241 - 443" title="Taxonomic circumscription of Diaporthales based on multigene phylogeny and morphology." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-018-0410-z" volume="93" year="2018">Senanayake et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BA6F6970A4ABE9849EF18501E399FD0E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.11" author="Crous, PW" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="291 - 473" refId="B4" refString="Crous, PW, Carnegie, AJ, Wingfield, MJ, et, al., 2019. Fungal Planet description sheets: 868-950. Persoonia 42: 291 - 473" title="Fungal Planet description sheets: 868 - 950." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.11" volume="42" year="2019">Crous et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7D8C1FF20D609DF0E9EAB827624CFA9A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.myc.2018.08.001" author="Minoshima, A" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="31 - 39" refId="B19" refString="Minoshima, A, Walker, DM, Takemoto, S, Hosoya, T, Walker, AK, Ishikawa, S, Hirooka, Y, 2019. Pathogenicity and taxonomy of Tenuignomoniastyracis gen. et sp. nov., a new monotypic genus of Gnomoniaceae on Styraxobassia in Japan. Mycoscience 60: 31 - 39" title="Pathogenicity and taxonomy of Tenuignomoniastyracis gen. et sp. nov., a new monotypic genus of Gnomoniaceae on Styraxobassia in Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.myc.2018.08.001" volume="60" year="2019">Minoshima et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
